│ The infinite recursion eventually leads to stack corruption and the segfault when accessing type information.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The root cause is in the                         │
│ `LoopGuards::collectFromBlock` function in ScalarEvolution.cpp. While there is a `MaxLoopGuardCollectionDepth` constant and a `Depth` parameter to prevent infinite recursion, the depth  │
│ check is only applied in a specific case (when collecting conditions from predecessor chains) but not at the general entry point of the function. When processing PHI nodes with          │
│ unreachable predecessors, the recursion depth isn't properly limited, leading to infinite recursion and eventual stack overflow/corruption.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): Add a depth     │
│ check at the beginning of `collectFromBlock` to prevent infinite recursion. The function already has a `Depth` parameter and `MaxLoopGuardCollectionDepth` constant, so we just need to   │
│ apply the depth limit universally.\n\n5. Conclusion: Adding the depth check at the start of `collectFromBlock` will prevent infinite recursion when processing problematic CFGs with      │
│ unreachable blocks, fixing the segfault while maintaining the existing functionality for valid cases. This is a minimal, targeted fix that addresses the root cause without affecting     │
│ normal operation."})                                                                                                                                                                      │
